OL,4,CHorizon was fine despite knowing faults
OL,6,FOn Friday, counsel to the inquiry Sam
OL,7,FStevens asked: "What did you think
OL,8,FPaula Vennells knew?"
OL,10,FDame Moya replied: "Gosh. I think she
OL,11,Fknew, on the basis of the evidence
OL,12,Fthat has emerged in this inquiry, that
OL,13,Fthere were faults in the system.
OL,15,F"I think that Post Office executives,
OL,16,Fincluding Mrs Vennells, continued to `
OL,17,Fslavishly, in my opinion ` adhere to
OL,18,Fthe position that was not tenable on
OL,19,Fthe basis of the evidence presented
OL,20,Fhere ` that there were no faults."
