OL,6,FAsked what she meant when she said Ms
OL,7,FVennells was "a good person and would
OL,8,Fnever accuse anyone in the wrong",
OL,9,FDame Moya said: "Mrs Vennells was
OL,10,Fbeing vilified in the press and we
OL,11,Fdidn't know at that time in 2022 what
OL,12,Fwe know now as a result of the
OL,13,Fevidence that has emerged in this
OL,14,Finquiry.
OL,16,F"So at that time, I can only say what
OL,17,FI saw ` and what I saw when I worked
OL,18,Fwith Mrs Vennells was a hard-working
OL,19,Fexecutive who was a problem solver.
OL,20,FNot at all the kind of person that she
OL,21,Fhas been portrayed (to be)."
